snippet.textDisplay:
Let’s just call a spade a spade.

The trilogy was a creative tug of war between two directors. The conclusion was a result of trying to undo all the bile that the previous episode spewed out, while trying to please fans at the same time.

It’s purely fan service trying to tie up everything once and for all. Not everyone will agree with it.

It wasn’t the best episode— but it wasn’t it wasn’t the worst episode either. I think the plot worked. I appreciated what they attempted to do, and I’m ultimately ok with how this saga ended.

I’ll probably get lynched in the comments for saying that... but I’m being realistic about this. It ended as well as it could. I’m just sad that the trilogy wasn’t given a better chance.

Sigh... okay, back to Mandalorian.
